<!-- ── BENCHMARK DESIGN ── -->
<section id="benchmark" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:36px">
      <div class="section-label">Benchmark Architecture</div>
      <div class="section-title">Reproducibility beats authority in a distributed system</div>
      <p class="section-sub">
        A benchmark that is theoretically better but intermittently unreachable from validator nodes is not a benchmark — it is an aspiration.
        The system is designed around this constraint.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bench-grid" style="margin-bottom:28px">
      <div class="bench-card live">
        <span class="bench-badge live">Live Benchmark</span>
        <div class="bench-card-title">Market Aggregate</div>
        <div class="bench-card-desc">
          <strong>Source:</strong> open.er-api.com · BOB/PEN<br/>
          <strong>Why:</strong> Consistently reachable across all 5 GenLayer validator nodes. Enables <code>strict_eq</code> consensus where every validator independently fetches and returns the same deterministically rounded result.<br/><br/>
          <strong>Benchmark ID:</strong> <code>MARKET-YYYYMMDD</code><br/>
          Each lock and roll records the exact source, rate, and timestamp on-chain.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bench-card audit">
        <span class="bench-badge audit">Audit Reference</span>
        <div class="bench-card-title">BCRP × BCB Cross</div>
        <div class="bench-card-desc" style="color:#7c5228">
          <strong>Source:</strong> Banco Central de Reserva del Perú (PEN/USD series PD04638PD) × Banco Central de Bolivia peg (6.96 BOB/USD fixed since 2012)<br/>
          <strong>Why retained:</strong> Provides official central-bank rate for reconciliation, audit, and institutional review. Off-chain reference, not the on-chain lock source.<br/><br/>
          <strong>Architecture path:</strong> A BCRP-accessible proxy would make this the live primary. Treated as an infrastructure upgrade — not a missing product feature.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:28px">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-bottom:16px">How to read this in the settlement console</div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;flex-wrap:wrap" class="bench-field-grid">
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px">Fields on every rate event</div>
          <div class="ic-grid">
            <div class="ic">
              <div class="ic-label">Benchmark Used</div>
              <div class="ic-value" style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:13px">MARKET_AGGREGATE</div>
              <div class="ic-sub">The actual source used for this lock</div>
            </div>
            <div class="ic">
              <div class="ic-label">Benchmark ID</div>
              <div class="ic-value" style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:13px">MARKET-20260306</div>
              <div class="ic-sub">Date-stamped, unique per event</div>
            </div>
            <div class="ic">
              <div class="ic-label">As Of</div>
              <div class="ic-value" style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:13px">2026-03-06T19:12Z</div>
              <div class="ic-sub">UTC timestamp from oracle</div>
            </div>
            <div class="ic">
              <div class="ic-label">Audit Reference</div>
              <div class="ic-value" style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--amber)">BCRP×BCB</div>
              <div class="ic-sub">Off-chain reconciliation rate</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:6px">Hierarchy logic</div>
          <div class="arch-row">
            <div class="arch-num">1</div>
            <div class="arch-content">
              <div class="arch-title">Try BCRP×BCB (primary)</div>
              <div class="arch-desc">All validators independently fetch BCRP API and compute cross via fixed BCB peg. If <code>strict_eq</code> consensus → use it, label <code>BCRP_BCB_CROSS</code>.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-row">
            <div class="arch-num">2</div>
            <div class="arch-content">
              <div class="arch-title">Fall back to market aggregate</div>
              <div class="arch-desc">If primary fails consensus (reachability disagreement), relayer immediately retries with <code>request_rate_lock_fallback</code>. No manual intervention. Label <code>MARKET_AGGREGATE</code>.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="arch-row" style="margin-bottom:0">
            <div class="arch-num">✕</div>
            <div class="arch-content">
              <div class="arch-title">Error only if both fail</div>
              <div class="arch-desc">No lock is delivered. Trade stays in <code>RATE_PENDING</code>. Relayer does not retry silently — caller sees an explicit failure with reason.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:20px;background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid rgba(21,128,61,0.2);border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:22px 28px">
      <div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:600;color:var(--green);margin-bottom:8px">The positioning in one sentence</div>
      <div style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;color:#166534">
        "GenLayer locks the settlement amount using a reproducible market benchmark available to all validators. Official central-bank rates are retained as an off-chain audit reference for reconciliation and review."
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── ORACLE ARCHITECTURE ── -->
<section id="architecture" class="section" style="background:var(--card)">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:36px">
      <div class="section-label">Architecture</div>
      <div class="section-title">Two chains, one settlement lifecycle</div>
      <p class="section-sub">GenLayer handles oracle consensus. Base Sepolia holds the state machine. A dedicated relayer bridges them.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Control flow diagram -->
    <div style="display:flex;gap:24px;margin-bottom:36px;flex-wrap:wrap">
      <!-- Main flow -->
      <div style="flex:1;min-width:300px">
        <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:1.2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:16px">Control Flow</div>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:flex-start;gap:0">
          <!-- Trade Contract -->
          <div style="background:#fff;border:1.5px solid var(--dark);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:16px 24px;width:100%;position:relative">
            <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:4px">Base Sepolia</div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:15px">Trade Contract</div>
            <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:4px">Holds state machine. Emits events. Accepts rate callbacks from relayer wallet only.</div>
          </div>
          <!-- Arrow down -->
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;width:48px;margin:0 24px">
            <div style="width:2px;height:14px;background:var(--muted)"></div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1">↓</div>
            <div style="width:2px;height:14px;background:var(--muted)"></div>
          </div>
          <!-- Benchmark Oracle -->
          <div style="background:#1a1817;border:1.5px solid #3d3b39;border-radius:var(--radius);padding:16px 24px;width:100%">
            <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:#5a5755;margin-bottom:4px">GenLayer Studionet</div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:15px;color:#fff">Benchmark Oracle</div>
            <div style="font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;margin-top:4px">5 validators fetch market rate independently. strict_eq consensus. Returns benchmark_type, benchmark_id, rate_18.</div>
          </div>
          <!-- Arrow down -->
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;width:48px;margin:0 24px">
            <div style="width:2px;height:14px;background:var(--muted)"></div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1">↓</div>
            <div style="width:2px;height:14px;background:var(--muted)"></div>
          </div>
          <!-- Settlement Engine -->
          <div style="background:#fff;border:1.5px solid var(--dark);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:16px 24px;width:100%">
            <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:4px">Base Sepolia</div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:15px">Settlement Engine</div>
            <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:4px">Applies rate to invoice. Computes settlement_amount. Stores roll records. State becomes RATE_LOCKED or ROLLED.</div>
          </div>
          <!-- Arrow down -->
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;width:48px;margin:0 24px">
            <div style="width:2px;height:14px;background:var(--muted)"></div>
            <div style="font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1">↓</div>
            <div style="width:2px;height:14px;background:var(--muted)"></div>
          </div>
          <!-- Payment Confirmation -->
          <div style="background:var(--green-light);border:1.5px solid rgba(21,128,61,0.3);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:16px 24px;width:100%">
            <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:var(--green);margin-bottom:4px">On-chain event</div>
            <div style="font-weight:700;font-size:15px;color:var(--green)">Payment Confirmation</div>
            <div style="font-size:13px;color:#166534;margin-top:4px">Settled event emitted with final amount, benchmark reference, and timestamp. Complete audit trail from events alone.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Side: optional + relayer -->
      <div style="width:240px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px">
        <div>
          <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:1.2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px">Relayer Bridge</div>
          <div style="background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:16px">
            <div style="font-weight:600;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:6px">fx-settlement-relayer</div>
            <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.6">Watches Base Sepolia events → calls GenLayer oracle → delivers callbacks. Dedicated wallet. Stateless between runs.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:1.2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px">Optional — not in main flow</div>
          <div style="background:var(--card);border:1px dashed var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:16px;opacity:0.7">
            <div style="font-weight:600;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:6px">Exception Handler</div>
            <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.6">exceptionFlagged + exceptionPaused flags. Orthogonal to lifecycle. Admin-controlled. Does not affect settlement math.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:1.2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:12px">Benchmark hierarchy</div>
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px">
            <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 12px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px">
              <span style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;background:var(--green-light);color:var(--green);padding:1px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-weight:700">1</span>
              <span style="font-size:13px;">BCRP×BCB cross</span>
            </div>
            <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 12px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px">
              <span style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;background:var(--blue-light);color:var(--blue);padding:1px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-weight:700">2</span>
              <span style="font-size:13px;">Market aggregate</span>
            </div>
            <div style="background:#fff;border:1px dashed var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 12px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;opacity:0.6">
              <span style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;background:var(--red-light);color:var(--red);padding:1px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-weight:700">✕</span>
              <span style="font-size:13px;">No lock delivered</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- GenLayer validator consensus -->
    <div class="console" style="margin-bottom:20px">
      <div class="console-bar">
        <div class="cdot cdot-r"></div><div class="cdot cdot-y"></div><div class="cdot cdot-g"></div>
        <span class="console-title">FxBenchmarkOracle.py — request_rate_lock_fallback result</span>
      </div>
      <div class="console-body">
        <div style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:#5a5755;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;margin-bottom:14px">Validator Results — open.er-api.com · BOB/PEN</div>
        <div class="v-grid" style="margin-bottom:20px">
          <div class="v-card">
            <div class="v-id">V1 · 0x57De</div>
            <div class="v-rate">0.493</div>
            <div class="v-source">open.er-api</div>
            <div class="v-agree disagree">disagree</div>
          </div>
          <div class="v-card">
            <div class="v-id">V2 · 0x6528</div>
            <div class="v-rate">0.493</div>
            <div class="v-source">open.er-api</div>
            <div class="v-agree agree">agree</div>
          </div>
          <div class="v-card">
            <div class="v-id">V3 · 0x6d55</div>
            <div class="v-rate">0.493</div>
            <div class="v-source">open.er-api</div>
            <div class="v-agree disagree">disagree</div>
          </div>
          <div class="v-card">
            <div class="v-id">V4 · 0x757F</div>
            <div class="v-rate">0.493</div>
            <div class="v-source">open.er-api</div>
            <div class="v-agree agree">agree</div>
          </div>
          <div class="v-card">
            <div class="v-id">V5 · 0x8729</div>
            <div class="v-rate">0.493</div>
            <div class="v-source">open.er-api</div>
            <div class="v-agree agree">agree</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="consensus-display">
          <div>
            <div class="cons-label">CONSENSUS RATE · BOB/PEN · strict_eq + deterministic round(rate,3)</div>
            <div class="cons-rate">0.493</div>
            <div class="cons-method">rate_18 = 493000000000000000 · benchmark_id = MARKET-20260306</div>
          </div>
          <div style="text-align:right">
            <span class="tag tag-green" style="margin-bottom:8px;display:inline-block">MAJORITY_AGREE</span><br/>
            <span style="font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:#5a5755">No LLM in rate comparison<br/>Arithmetic only</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top:12px;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:11px;color:#5a5755">
          Note: 2 validators disagreed in this run — studionet validators are heterogeneous. MAJORITY_AGREE (3/5) is sufficient for a valid lock.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Design principles -->
    <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius-xl);padding:28px">
      <div class="section-label" style="margin-bottom:20px">Design Choices</div>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:20px;flex-wrap:wrap" class="design-grid">
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:15px">strict_eq, not LLM compare</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">All 5 validators independently fetch + compute. Round to nearest 0.001 before comparison. Zero LLM in the numeric path — arithmetic is deterministic, language models are not.</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:15px">One-way rate lock</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">Once RATE_LOCKED, the rate cannot be silently overwritten. A roll is a distinct economic event with a full RollRecord on-chain: prior rate, new rate, prior due, new due, benchmark used, roll cost.</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:15px">Exception is orthogonal</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">exceptionFlagged is a bool flag, not a status branch. Lifecycle continues unless admin explicitly sets exceptionPaused=true. No hidden state blocking settlement.</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:15px">Dedicated relayer wallet</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">oracleRelayer (0x7b97…) is separate from the exporter/deployer wallet (0xe963…). Role separation is enforced at the contract constructor — not a convention.</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:15px">Machine-readable artifacts</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">deployment.json and deployment.env are emitted by the deploy script. The frontend requires no hand-editing to connect to a fresh deployment. All addresses, ABIs, and metadata are in the manifest.</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div style="font-weight:700;margin-bottom:6px;font-size:15px">Events reconstruct lifecycle</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">RateLockRequested, RateLocked, RollRequested, RateRolled, Settled — a frontend can reconstruct the complete trade lifecycle from events alone. No off-chain state required.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── HOW IT WORKS ── -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div style="margin-bottom:36px">
      <div class="section-label">How It Works</div>
      <div class="section-title">Create → Lock Rate → Settle or Extend</div>
    </div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">01 —</div>
        <div class="step-icon" style="background:var(--blue-light);color:var(--blue)">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="step-title">Create the Settlement</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Exporter deploys TradeFxSettlement with invoice amount (BOB), due date, exporter, and importer addresses. The <em>oracleRelayer</em> address is locked at construction — the contract will only accept rate callbacks from this wallet.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">02 —</div>
        <div class="step-icon" style="background:var(--green-light);color:var(--green)">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="step-title">Lock the Rate</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Exporter calls <code>requestRateLock()</code>. The relayer detects the event, calls FxBenchmarkOracle on GenLayer (trying BCRP first, falling back to market aggregate), then delivers <code>receiveRate()</code> with the benchmark metadata. Settlement amount is computed and locked.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">03 —</div>
        <div class="step-icon" style="background:var(--amber-light);color:var(--amber)">
          <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="17 1 21 5 17 9"/><path d="M3 11V9a4 4 0 0 1 4-4h14"/><polyline points="7 23 3 19 7 15"/><path d="M21 13v2a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H3"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="step-title">Settle or Extend Hedge</div>
        <div class="step-desc">If the due date approaches, either party calls <code>requestRoll(newDueDate)</code>. The relayer fetches a fresh benchmark and delivers <code>receiveRolledRate()</code>. Roll cost is 0 (spot re-lock). The RollRecord is stored permanently on-chain.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

